[Black "The Aggressive 6.Be2 without O-O #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3
{ White indicates they want to go for d4 and the Open Sicilian. } 2... d6
{ Black's most popular move at the top level because of its flexibility, and definitely the move we want to play if we intend to go into a Dragon setup. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6
{ Preparing to fianchetto our pride and joy - the Dragon bishop. } 6. Be2
{ We will study in-depth, separately, the lines where White either castles short or long. In general, we will try to react with ...d5 whenever we are allowed to.   Every different variation that White can choose has its nuances, although they are similar and we must make the effort to memorize and understand them correctly in order not to get confused while playing the game. }
6... Bg7 7. Be3 O-O 8. O-O Nc6 9. Nb3
{ The typical move to avoid ...d5.   Against  9.f4  we reply directly with the dangerous  9...Qb6  , while against the others we  will break with ...d5. }
9... Be6 10. f4 Rc8
{ My favorite reply. We will fight for the c4-square and we will show how to use the move ...e5 to give our knight that square.   It will be very important to learn these two situations: when our d6-pawn is weak and when to go for the typical exchange sacrifice on c3. }
