{ Preparing to fianchetto our pride and joy - the Dragon bishop. } 6. Be2
{ We will study in-depth, separately, the lines where White either castles short or long. In general, we will try to react with ...d5 whenever we are allowed to.   Every different variation that White can choose has its nuances, although they are similar and we must make the effort to memorize and understand them correctly in order not to get confused while playing the game. }
6... Bg7 7. Be3 O-O 8. Qd2 Nc6 9. O-O-O
{ This variation has been played by very strong players to get off the beaten path but still keep some initiative. Although  9...Ng4  is very playable, we will show that breaking  with ...d5 helps us to achieve good positions. }
9... d5 10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Nxd5
