20... Kxg7 21. Nxh5+ gxh5 22. Nxd5 Be6
{ To solidify the position, we continue with ...f6 and ...Kf7 in order to be able to play ...Qg8 and attack the g2-pawn. We can also gain space on the queenside with ...a5 followed by ...b4. }
