16. Kb1 { Delaying b3 gives us an additional option. } 16... b5 17. b3 b4
{ The b-pawn gets to b4 on time! } 18. Na4
{ The only viable square for the knight. } 18... Rc7 { ...Bd7 is coming. } 19.
Nf4 Bd7 20. Nb2 { The knight heads to c4 or d3, attacking b4. } 20... Bc6
{ Covering d5 to prevent Bxf6 followed by Nd5 ideas. } 21. Nbd3 a5
{ White should take advantage of the fact that we're not castled to break in the center since we're only one move away from being more than fine. }
22. e5 dxe5 23. Nxe5 Ne4
{ The key defensive move! We unleash the bishop's fury along the long diagonal, but it's far from over. Let's see how play could continue:   24.Rxe4  Bxe4  25.fxe4  Bxe5  26.Qd5  is the idea behind the exchange sacrifice.  26...Bc3  27.Nxg6  fxg6  28.Qe6  Kf8  with the idea of meeting 29.Qxg6 with 29...Qe8.  29.Rf1+  Ke8  ,  we'll hide the king on the queenside if White allows us to do so.  30.Rd1  Kf8  with a draw! }
