20. Nc3 a5
{ We also want to play on the queenside! I like Black's chances with the open b-file. Let's see how play could continue:   21.Nxd5  Bxd5  22.b3  ,  avoiding the trick on a2 and giving some luft to the king.  22...a4  ,  we want to coordinate the attack on the open a-file with the queen on f6 as soon as possible.  23.Qxe7  only leads to a drawn endgame, but White has nothing more than allowing this.  23...Qxe7  24.Rxe7  axb3  25.axb3  Bxb3  , the key move.  26.Rxd8+  Rxd8  27.cxb3  Rd1+  28.Kb2  Rxf1  and the game will end in a draw in a few moves. }
