12. Bxd4 Qxd5 13. Bxg7 Qxd1 14. Raxd1 Kxg7 15. Bf3
{ White harasses us on b7 to keep the game alive. } 15... Be6
{ We don't have to calculate a lot to see that  16.Bxb7  is answered by  16...Rab8  ,  entering on the 7th rank next. }
16. b3 Rac8 { Removing the rook from the long diagonal and hitting c2. } 17. c4
b6 { No problems left. The position is even. } *

