11... Ne8 12. f4 f6 { A second central pawn break in a few moves. } 13. exf6
Bxf6 { 13...Nxf6  is also a completely acceptable alternative. } 14. Qd2 Ng7
15. Rad1 Qc7
{ We have a nice position in front of us and several interesting plans at our disposal. We can go for ...Re8 followed by ...e5, bring our knight to f5 and the bishop to a6, or we can even calculate if ...d4 followed by ...Rd8 is a good option. }
