{ White is going their own way! } 11... b4 { And we go ours! } 12. Na4
{ I don't think any player will play this move calmly as White because the knight is, obviously, on a bad square. Without hesitation, let's go for it! }
12... Bd7 { Why hiding our intentions? } 13. a3
{ The best way to try to save the knight. } 13... Qc7
{ A fine move that improves our queen and controls e5. In addition, in view of the imminent trade on b4, we take the opportunity to attack c2. }
14. axb4 Nxb4 15. c3 Nc6
{ White has managed to defend the knight but is still unable to give it a better life. Here, it is difficult to find ideas to improve White's position while we do have various plans to tilt the balance in our favor.   We can play with ...Rab8 to put pressure on the b-file, take the f8-rook to d8 to threaten at some point, after ...Be8, to play ...d5 and ...Ne4, or play ...Na5 at the right moment to emphasize the weakness of the knight on a4. }
