{ The typical move in these positions, but we'll show that we're better prepared to fight for the center. }
13... b4 { Asking the knight what its intentions are. } 14. Nd5 Nxd5 15. Qxd5
{ Taking with the pawn does not help at all because after ...Ne7, we're immediately putting pressure on d5 and White doesn't have enough dynamism to pose any problems. }
15... a5
{ Intending to go ...a4 next, with the idea of getting the d4-square for our knight. }
16. Rad1
{ This move seems natural, putting pressure on d6, but White lacks tempi. }
16... a4 17. Nc1 Na5 { Getting to c4. White's position crumbles. } *

