7. O-O O-O 8. Re1
{ A solid line that which gained some popularity among the more solid players. }
8... Nc6 9. Nb3
{ A solid line that aims to hide the bishop on c1 and put a knight on d5. }
9... Be6
{ 9...Ne5  followed by ...Ng4 is also a perfectly playable alternative. } 10.
Bf1 d5 { Once more, if we can strike in the center, let's do it! } 11. exd5
Nxd5 { In these types of positions, we are never going to have problems. } 12.
Nxd5 Bxd5
{ Taking with the queen is somewhat more solid, but I think we can keep the queens on the board and play for more. }
13. c3
{ A necessary move because the bishop on g7 was already pointing at b2. } 13...
e5 14. Be3 b6 { It's important to control the c5-square. } 15. Qd2 Ne7
{ Defending the bishop to be able to play ...Qc7 and occupy the d-file with one of the rooks. }
16. Bh6 Qc7 17. Bxg7 Kxg7 { Black has a very healthy position. } *

