{ This is precisely what Black wants to achieve. For the sake of respecting the time of those of you reading this course, I am not going to analyze  10.g3  since Black's reply and concept is exactly the same as those of this line. }
10... Nxe3 11. fxe3 Kg7
{ Black protects f7 with ...Rf8 and then we will have several interesting plans, my favorite being ...Nd7-f6 followed by ...Bd7-c6, with good play. }
12. Qd2 Nd7 13. Bxd7
{ A bit strange option, but justified, after which the knight on f6 is really annoying! }
13... Bxd7 14. Nf3
{ And now the best thing to do is to be drastic and get rid of complexes! }
14... Bxc3 { We give up the bishop in exchange for being solid. } 15. Qxc3+ f6
{ We have the position under control. However, we will go deeper into this line so that you don't panic while playing the game. }
16. e5 { This move is possible, as we cannot take twice. } 16... dxe5 17. Nxe5
Rc8
{ Taking the knight would be a very serious mistake that would lead us to lose the game. However, we can continue with a clever move. }
18. Qb3 Be8
{ Defending on f7 and forcing the knight's retreat. We can look forward to a nice endgame with some queenside pressure. }
