{ It has cost me a lot to recommend this move. However, after not little time analyzing the position, I am convinced that it is the most practical one.   The move has many flaws: it trades our powerful bishop, fixes White's pawn structure, we lose the only piece we don't have on the eighth rank... but it definitely stops White's dynamism and we are going to focus on trying to convert our extra pawn. The Dragon's bishop sacrifices itself as a hero! }
