13. g4
{ Preventing the black knight from reaching f6 is something suggested by itself. }
13... Re8 14. g5 Nb6
{ Once the f6-square has been taken from us, we look for another route! The knight, in addition to threatening to jump to c4, reinforces d5 to be able to play ...c5 when we consider it appropriate and finally, leaves free the diagonal to the bishop on c8. }
15. h4 Bg4
{ Without letting White even dream of attacking, that's the way to go! Black's position is very favorable. }
