{ Once White's knight has left c3, we go to the e4-square with ours. } 16. Bd3
Bf5 17. Bxf5 gxf5
{ Although our structure is 'ugly', it is not important because it will not be possible to attack the f5-pawn with our knight on e4, and it is more likely for us than for White to be able to use the g-file. }
