{ Let's hit the pawn. } 19. Ra4 { Defending indirectly the d4-pawn. } 19... Qb6
{ More fuel to the fire. } 20. Rxb4
{ 20.e5  Bd7  would immediately transpose to the analyzed line. } 20... Qxb4
{ The pressure on d4 forces White to go all-in, unless they want to give up the b2-pawn. }
21. e5 Bd7
{ Preparing ...Rc8. Black's pieces are clearly more active than White's. } *

