[SetUp "1"]

{ This test is a bit of strategy, and a bit of tactics. How should we react to this check? }
11... Kf8
{ Running to the safety of the kingside where we can artificially castle if needed.   11...Bd7  would be a very poor choice as after  12.Bxd7+  Kxd7  ,  our king will remain in the center for a long time to come, as  12...Nxd7  loses to  13.Bxh8  . }
12. Bc4 Be6
{ Again, offering the exchange of bishops on e6, when we don't mind having an extra central pawn. }
13. Bxe6 fxe6 14. O-O e5 15. Be3 Bxe3 16. Qxe3 Rc8
{ We have fantastic prospects in this position and easy play with our queenside minority. }
