[SetUp "1"]

{ White thinks they have a central initiative. How did Black prove this theory incorrect? }
20... a4 { Whoops! The bishop is trapped. } 21. Bb4
{ 21.exf6  Bxf6  and the unopposed light-squared bishop will wreak havoc on White's position. }
21... axb3 22. Nxb3 Rd5 23. exf6
{ After  23.Rxd5  Nxd5  ,  Black is again up a piece. } 23... Rxd1+ 24. Rxd1
Bxf6
{ Black is up an important pawn, has the bishop pair, and a continuing attack. They went on to win the game convincingly. }
