[SetUp "1"]

{ The d5-square can often look tempting for White to make use of early, but they have to be sure it's working tactically. How did Black punish this early jump? }
12... Nxd5 { 12...a4  is good as well, but let's focus on the game. } 13. Bxd5
{ 13.exd5  a4  traps the bishop. } 13... e6
{ Giving the bishop no good options. } 14. Bg5
{ 14.Bxb7  Nc4  15.Qd3  Nxe3  16.Qxe3  Rb8  is the start of a devastating queenside initiative, particularly because our dark-squared bishop is unopposed. White clearly didn't like the look of this. }
14... Qb6 15. Be3 exd5 { Black won a piece and soon the game. } *

