[SetUp "1"]

13. Bh6
{ White has played a slight inaccuracy with Bh6 - a natural move, trying to remove a key defender from our kingside. How did Simon respond? }
13... Bxh6
{ The best move, creating ideal circumstances for our counterplay by drawing the queen away from the queenside.   13...b4  14.Nd5  Will likely end poorly for Black since White is able to remove our key defender on f6. }
14. Qxh6 Rxc3
{ The natural follow-up, starting quick counterplay against the white king. }
15. bxc3 Qa5 16. hxg6 fxg6 17. g5 Nh5
{ The only move, and a good move - blocking White's attack. Now White will have to either go all in or defend. }
